Do you remember the horrific American Medical Collection Agency (Retrieval-Masters Creditors Bureau Inc.) breach in 2019?  You can refresh your memory by scrolling through the Related posts below this one, but TL;DR: LabCorp was one of AMCA&#8217;s clients that was affected by the breach, and in July 2019, they notified HHS that 10,251,784 patients had...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F06%2F12%2Flabcorp-reaches-35m-settlement-over-american-medical-collection-agency-breach%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dlabcorp-reaches-35m-settlement-over-american-medical-collection-agency-breach&amp;action_name=Labcorp%20reaches%20%2435M%20settlement%20over%20American%20Medical%20Collection%20Agency%20breach&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
