Lawrence Abrams reports: A Ukrainian national extradited from Ireland to the United States last year has pleaded guilty to conspiracy charges tied to the Conti ransomware operation. The U.S. Department of Justice announced Thursday that 44-year-old Oleksii Oleksiyovych Lytvynenko pleaded guilty to conspiracy to commit wire fraud for his role in Conti ransomware attacks conducted...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F06%2F12%2Fukrainian-national-pleads-guilty-to-role-in-conti-ransomware-operation%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dukrainian-national-pleads-guilty-to-role-in-conti-ransomware-operation&amp;action_name=Ukrainian%20national%20pleads%20guilty%20to%20role%20in%20Conti%20ransomware%20operation&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
